<GuideLayout
  title="How to Play Bullet Force – Complete Beginner's Guide (2025)"
  description="New to Bullet Force? This beginner's guide covers game modes, controls, tips, perks, scorestreaks, and how to win your first match."
  schema={schema}
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Guides', href: '/guides' }, { label: 'How to Play' }]}
  toc={toc}
>
  <h1>How to Play Bullet Force – Complete Beginner's Guide</h1>

  <p>
    New to <strong>Bullet Force</strong>? This guide covers everything: how to start, all game modes, basic controls, the perk system, scorestreak setup, and tips to win your first few matches.
  </p>

  <h2 id="what-is">What Is Bullet Force?</h2>
  <p>
    Bullet Force is a free multiplayer first-person shooter developed by <strong>Blayze Games</strong>. It plays like a classic call-of-duty style FPS — two teams battle across 5 maps with customizable weapon loadouts, perks, and scorestreaks.
    The game runs in your browser on PC and Chromebook (no download), and also as a native app on Android and iOS.
  </p>

  <h2 id="start">How to Start Playing Bullet Force</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Open the game</strong> — go to CrazyGames, Poki, or the <a href="/play">play page</a>. No download or install required on PC.</li>
    <li><strong>Register or Guest</strong> — click "Register" to create a free account (recommended — saves your progress) or "Guest" to play immediately. See the <a href="/account">Account Guide</a>.</li>
    <li><strong>Click Multiplayer</strong> — from the main lobby, click Multiplayer to enter public matchmaking.</li>
    <li><strong>Select your loadout</strong> — choose a primary weapon, secondary, perk, and scorestreak before the match starts. Beginners: pick the M4A1 if available.</li>
    <li><strong>Play</strong> — WASD to move, right-click to aim, left-click to shoot. Follow your team and earn kills.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="game-modes">Bullet Force Game Modes Explained</h2>

  <h3>Team Deathmatch (TDM)</h3>
  <p>Two teams (usually 6v6) compete to reach the kill limit first. Standard FPS format. The team that reaches the target score first wins. <strong>Best mode for beginners</strong> — focus on getting kills and staying alive.</p>

  <h3>Free For All (FFA)</h3>
  <p>Every player fights for themselves. First player to the kill limit wins. Good for practicing aim without team coordination pressure.</p>

  <h3>Conquest</h3>
  <p>Two teams capture and hold flag objectives on the map. Score increases when your team controls more flags. <strong>More strategic</strong> — you need to push objectives, not just kill-farm.</p>

  <h3>Gun Game</h3>
  <p>All players start with the same weapon (usually a pistol). Each kill upgrades you to the next weapon in the progression. The first player to get a kill with the final weapon wins. Great for weapon variety practice.</p>

  <h3>Campaign (Offline)</h3>
  <p>Single-player missions against AI bots. Good for learning map layouts and controls before jumping into competitive multiplayer.</p>

  <h2 id="controls">Basic Controls (PC)</h2>
  <p>Here are the essential controls to know before your first match:</p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Action</th><th>Key</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Move</td><td><code>W A S D</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Sprint</td><td><code>Shift</code> (hold)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Jump</td><td><code>Space</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Crouch</td><td><code>Ctrl</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Shoot (Hip Fire)</td><td><code>Left Click</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Aim Down Sights</td><td><code>Right Click</code> (hold)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Reload</td><td><code>R</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Knife / Melee</td><td><code>V</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Throw Grenade</td><td><code>G</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td>Switch Weapons</td><td><code>1</code> / <code>2</code> / <code>Q</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>See the full <a href="/guides/controls">Controls & Keybinds Guide</a> for every key and rebinding instructions.</p>

  <h2 id="perks">Bullet Force Perks Explained</h2>
  <p>Perks are passive abilities that modify your character's performance. You equip one perk per loadout slot before a match.</p>

  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Perk</th><th>Effect</th><th>Best For</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Lightweight</td><td>Increases movement speed</td><td>Aggressive flankers, SMG users</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Flak Jacket</td><td>Reduces explosive damage taken</td><td>Grenade-heavy maps, objective modes</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Ghost</td><td>Hidden from enemy UAV</td><td>Stealth players, flankers</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Scavenger</td><td>Refill ammo from dead enemies</td><td>Long matches, high kill-rate players</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Hardline</td><td>Scorestreaks require 1 fewer kill</td><td>Players who want more frequent scorestreaks</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Dead Silence</td><td>Quieter footsteps</td><td>Stealth, map awareness players</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2 id="first-match">First Match Tips for Beginners</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Stay with teammates</strong> — lone wolves get picked off fast. Follow the map and stay near 1–2 allies at all times.</li>
    <li><strong>Use cover constantly</strong> — never stand in open areas. Move from cover to cover; pop out to shoot and return to safety.</li>
    <li><strong>ADS at medium range</strong> — right-click to aim before firing beyond 10 meters. Hip fire only at very close range.</li>
    <li><strong>Pick up weapons</strong> — press F to pick up weapons from eliminated enemies. Great way to access guns you haven't unlocked.</li>
    <li><strong>Start with the M4A1</strong> — once you've saved 4,000 credits, the M4A1 assault rifle is the best beginner weapon in the game.</li>
    <li><strong>Watch your minimap</strong> — red dots show enemy positions (when UAV is active). Rotate before enemies reach you.</li>
    <li><strong>Don't chase kills into danger</strong> — dying cancels your killstreak progress. Living longer is better than getting one more kill.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="with-friends">How to Play Bullet Force with Friends</h2>
  <p>
    Bullet Force uses a <strong>Custom Room</strong> system to play with specific people:
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>One player clicks <strong>Multiplayer → Custom Room → Create</strong> and sets a room name + password.</li>
    <li>Share the room name and password with your friends.</li>
    <li>Friends click <strong>Join Room</strong>, enter the room name and password to join.</li>
    <li>The room host can set team assignments and fill empty slots with public players or bots.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 id="rank-up">How Do I Rank Up Fast in Bullet Force?</h2>
  <p>Ranking up in Bullet Force is based on XP earned per match. To rank up faster:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Play TDM</strong> — Team Deathmatch gives the most XP per hour for active kill-focused players.</li>
    <li><strong>Use XP boosts</strong> if available in the shop during events.</li>
    <li><strong>Aim for high kill games</strong> — XP is awarded primarily per kill, plus match completion bonuses.</li>
    <li><strong>Play Conquest for objective XP</strong> — capturing flags gives bonus XP on top of kill XP.</li>
    <li><strong>Get scorestreaks</strong> — UAV assists and helicopter kills add XP on top of direct kills.</li>
  </ul>

